x4freetext: .LU-100 at the Institute For High Energy
Physics in Serpukhuv (Russia)
The Proton Beam and Irradiation Times Used were-
20 Nanoamperies and 3-5 Hour For Pb Foils,
36 Nanoamperies and 1 Hour For Nai Pellets,
20 Nanoamperies and 3 Hour For Rbcl Pellets.
The  stacks  were  repeatedly measured over a
period of several day.
In the Calculation of the Cross Sections the Following
Errors have Been Taken Into Account-
The Error in the primary incident energy of the
proton beam.
The error in the total number of protons on the
targets (mainly due to the error of the monitor
reactions) in the stack.
The error in the target thickness for foils.
The error in the target thickness for pellets.
The statistical error in the integrated
area of the photo-peaks.
The error in the counting statistics.
The error in the absolute efficiency of the
germanium detector.
The error in the attenuation corrections.
The error in the decay-data.
The Error in the counting geometry.
The error of irradiation and decay times.
/by Authors/.The Proton Energy is Average Proton Energy
At the Mid Thickness of Rb-Cl Discs.
The Pellets Made from Natural Rb-Cl (RB-85-72.17%,
Target. The Pellets Thicknesses were Determined by
Weight and Area Measurements. The Stack of 20 Rb-Cl
Pellets were Used.
.The Uncertainty is Reported by Authors.

x4freetext: The Irradiated Pb-206 Target was Kept For Period of
Time -33Hours- Sufficient For the Accumulation of the
Maximum Activity of Tl-201 from the Parent Products
Via the Decay Chain-Bi-201-M,G-Pb-201-Tl-201.There are
Measured the Cumulative Activity of Tl-201 Being the
Sum Activities Induced Via Direct Formation in the
(P,PXN) And (P,AXN) Reactions and Through the Bi-201-M
And Bi-201-G Decay.
A Stacked Foil Target -Thin Circular Foils 10 mm in
Diameter with Thickness Which Varied from 0.15-0.20
Mg/Cm**2- Was Constructed Using Enriched Metallic Lead.
The Isotopic Composition of the Pb-206 Foil-
Each Stack Consisted of 3 Foils /Triad/ with 3
Different Pb Isotopes-Pb-206,Pb-207 and Pb-208.A Total
Of 20 Triad =60 Foils with Total Mass 11 G/Cm**2- Were
Used.
Target was Measured 4-5 Times at Least and the Final
Result was the Weighted Average of the Measurements.
